This paper is about improving the performance of training Random Forest models on modern CPU architectures. It involves designing a novel algorithm and proposing optimizations to alleviate CPU performance bottlenecks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
